body:
#### Summary
When using `AbstractIterableAssert.zipSatisfy()`, any assertion failures are reported with the object's `toString()` method instead of using the provided `Representation`. It seems like that should apply to this situation.

#### Example
Output is:
```
java.lang.AssertionError: 
Expecting zipped elements of:
  <[SO representation (1, 2), SO representation (11, 22)]>
and:
  <[AO representation (1, 2), AO representation (111, 222)]>
to satisfy given requirements but these zipped elements did not:

- (SO toString (11, 22), AO toString (111, 222)) error: expected:<"11[1]"> but was:<"11[]">
```
Code: 
```java
public class Example {
  @Test
  public void testZipSatisfy() {
    List<SomeObject> sos = Arrays.asList(new SomeObject("1", "2"), new SomeObject("11", "22"));
    List<AnotherObject> aos = Arrays.asList(new AnotherObject("1", "2"), new AnotherObject("111", "222"));
    
    Assertions.useRepresentation(new Represent());
    assertThat(sos).zipSatisfy(aos, (actual, ao) -> {
      assertThat(actual.one).isEqualTo(ao.one);
      assertThat(actual.two).isEqualTo(ao.two);
    });
  }
  
  
  public static class AnotherObject {
    public String one;
    public String two;
    
    public AnotherObject(String one, String two) {
      this.one = one;
      this.two = two;
    }
    
    @Override
    public String toString() {
      return "AO toString (" + one + ", " + two + ")";
    }
    
  }
  public static class SomeObject {
    public String one;
    public String two;

    public SomeObject(String one, String two) {
      this.one = one;
      this.two = two;
    }

    @Override
    public String toString() {
      return "SO toString (" + one + ", " + two + ")";
    }
    
  }
  public static class Represent extends StandardRepresentation {
    @Override
    protected String fallbackToStringOf(Object object) {
      if (object instanceof SomeObject) {
        SomeObject s = (SomeObject) object;
        return "SO representation (" + s.one + ", " + s.two + ")";
      } else if (object instanceof AnotherObject) {
        AnotherObject s = (AnotherObject) object;
        return "AO representation (" + s.one + ", " + s.two + ")";
      }
      return super.fallbackToStringOf(object);
    }
  }
}
```
